The paper deals with a learning problem involving pairwise preferences, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of active learning algorithms is also a common technique in these fields. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with ranking and ordering, which is a topic in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
